00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:04.240
Welcome back to Movie Recaps.
Today I will show you a crime, drama,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:04.240 --> 00:00:09.920
horror film from 2009, titled The Loved Ones.
Spoilers ahead! Watch out and take care.

00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:14.240
The film opens with Brent, a teenage boy&nbsp;
driving through the countryside with his&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:14.240 --> 00:00:18.400
father Dan in his old car. While teasing each&nbsp;
other over the state of the vehicle and their&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:18.400 --> 00:00:22.160
tastes in music, Dan takes out and lights&nbsp;
a cigarette, which Brent disapproves of.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:22.720 --> 00:00:26.960
Distracted by his father's actions, Brent doesn't&nbsp;
see the person standing in the middle of the road&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:26.960 --> 00:00:31.600
until Dan calls attention to him. Brent manages&nbsp;
to dodge the stranger at the last second,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:37.200
but the car crashes against a tree, killing Dan.
Six months later, we find Brent at school chatting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:42.000
with his best friend Jamie. They discuss their&nbsp;
plans for prom, and Jamie shares some plant and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:46.400
protection with Brent, encouraging his friend&nbsp;
to have fun. The moment is interrupted when a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:51.200
classmate of theirs and certified goth, Mia, walks&nbsp;
in to use her locker, completely ignoring the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:51.200 --> 00:00:56.640
presence of both boys next to her. Jamie stares&nbsp;
at her, speechless and obviously infatuated.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:56.640 --> 00:01:00.880
After Mia leaves, Brent nudges into Jamie&nbsp;
following her, and he does exactly that,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:05.120
only to return seconds later with exciting&nbsp;
news: she's accepted his invitation to prom.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:10.400
Another girl walks in then: Lola, a shy-looking&nbsp;
gal, who asks Brent to go to prom with her.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.400 --> 00:01:14.160
Brent turns her down as politely as he can&nbsp;
since he's going with Holly, his girlfriend.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:14.800 --> 00:01:17.600
Lola doesn't react, but she's&nbsp;
quite obviously not pleased.&nbsp;

00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:21.840
After classes are done, Brent leaves the&nbsp;
school to meet with Holly at the doors,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:21.840 --> 00:01:26.080
who offers a ride because she's finally passed&nbsp;
her driving test. Brent asks her to guess who&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:26.080 --> 00:01:30.720
has invited him to the dance but doesn't offer&nbsp;
an answer. They end up making out in Holly's car,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:35.120
where she keeps asking for the answer to his&nbsp;
previous question. He doesn't reply at first,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:39.840
asking for more layers of clothes to be lost&nbsp;
before he replies. When Holly takes off his shirt,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:44.160
we get to see various scars on Brent's body&nbsp;
and a razor blade hanging on his necklace.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:44.160 --> 00:01:47.920
Cutting and smoking seem to be the method Brent&nbsp;
has chosen to deal with the trauma and guilt&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:47.920 --> 00:01:52.720
left by his father's death. As their making out&nbsp;
becomes more intimate, the couple becomes unaware&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:57.280
of their surroundings and, most importantly, of&nbsp;
the fact Lola is outside the car watching them&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:57.280 --> 00:02:02.080
through the window with increasing irritation.
A couple of hours later, Holly drives Brent to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:05.760
his house and asks him if he should pick him up&nbsp;
there for prom, since his mother doesn't know&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:10.720
she's gotten her license yet. It seems Brent and&nbsp;
cars are a touchy topic in the household, but he&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:10.720 --> 00:02:15.200
promises he'll tell her later. He doesn't return&nbsp;
Holly's "I love you" but as he gets off the car,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:19.120
he finally shares with her the answer to his&nbsp;
question: it was Lola who invited him to prom.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:19.680 --> 00:02:23.200
After Holly is gone, he enters his&nbsp;
house and goes directly to his room,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:23.200 --> 00:02:27.760
where he is writing some stuff down in the dark&nbsp;
while listening to heavy metal music. His mother,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:27.760 --> 00:02:33.040
Carla, interrupts him, expressing disapproval when&nbsp;
she learns Holly will be driving Brent to prom.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:33.040 --> 00:02:36.640
The way she words things makes Brent think&nbsp;
she blames him for his father's death.&nbsp;

00:02:36.640 --> 00:02:40.720
Feeling angry and frustrated after such a talk,&nbsp;
Brent leaves the house together with his dog,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:40.720 --> 00:02:44.720
heavy metal music playing on his earbuds and the&nbsp;
necklace held so tightly in his fist that it hurts&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:44.720 --> 00:02:49.280
him. He should be getting ready for prom (as we&nbsp;
see Holly doing in her own place) but instead&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:49.280 --> 00:02:53.520
he enters a rocky, isolated area where he starts&nbsp;
climbing a cliff and enjoying the thrill of the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:53.520 --> 00:02:58.240
danger. Once he makes it to the top, he smokes&nbsp;
while listening to his music, which doesn't allow&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:58.240 --> 00:03:03.120
him to hear his dog barking angrily at something.&nbsp;
His mother tries to reach him on his phone, but he&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:07.040
ignores the call just as a figure approaches him&nbsp;
from behind and covers his face with a piece of&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:11.600
cloth, intending to knock him out. Brent tries to&nbsp;
fight back with no luck and during the struggle,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:11.600 --> 00:03:15.440
his phone is kicked away. The stranger&nbsp;
takes a sleeping Brent away on their truck.&nbsp;

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:21.600
Meanwhile, back in town, Jamie is picking Mia up&nbsp;
at her house. She doesn't look very excited at&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:25.760
the prospect of prom, only getting more annoyed&nbsp;
when her mother and father -a police officer-&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:30.480
ask them to wait so they can take a picture. In&nbsp;
another part of town, we see a very excited Holly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:30.480 --> 00:03:35.120
arriving at Brent's place, only to be approached&nbsp;
by his mother, who a moment ago was at the cliffs,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:35.120 --> 00:03:39.840
worriedly looking for her son. She asks Holly&nbsp;
if she's seen Brent, but we all know she hasn't.&nbsp;

00:03:40.560 --> 00:03:43.440
Night falls. Jamie and Mia&nbsp;
are on their way to prom.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:44.080 --> 00:03:47.280
Holly and Carla continue to try to&nbsp;
reach Brent on the phone to no avail,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:47.280 --> 00:03:52.000
but they finally get a clue when they hear whining&nbsp;
outside: Brent's dog is back and he's quite hurt.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:57.040
Carla calls Mia's father, Mr. Valentine, to tell&nbsp;
him about what happened, but the cop doesn't take&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:57.040 --> 00:04:01.520
her seriously at first since Brent disappears&nbsp;
for hours often. During this conversation,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:01.520 --> 00:04:07.040
his wife shows obvious distress, as if this&nbsp;
brought back old, painful memories. Mr. Valentine&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:10.960
changes his mind and takes the problem seriously&nbsp;
when Carle tells him their dog had been stabbed.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:15.600
Said dog is now in Holly's car, who is trying&nbsp;
to take him to the vet while Carla talks to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:15.600 --> 00:04:19.840
the police officer, but she stops the car when&nbsp;
she realized the dog hasn't survived the trip.&nbsp;

00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:25.280
Two different cars are followed next: first,&nbsp;
Jamie's. He and Mia have made it to prom and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:25.280 --> 00:04:30.000
they enter the school ground together, although&nbsp;
Mia is obviously not in her best condition. The&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:33.520
other car is the truck that kidnapped Brent,&nbsp;
which is stopped in the middle of the road so&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:33.520 --> 00:04:37.440
its driver can pick up the dead animal. The&nbsp;
truck then goes on until they make it to a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:37.440 --> 00:04:41.200
house in the middle of the countryside, and&nbsp;
when the canvas covering the back is lifted,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:41.200 --> 00:04:46.320
the kidnappers are finally revealed: it's Lola&nbsp;
and her father, Eric. Lola is worried that Brent&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:46.320 --> 00:04:50.480
may've died but Eric checks his pulse and assures&nbsp;
her he isn't, which makes her bend over Brent&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:50.480 --> 00:04:54.320
