00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:02.960
well while her father throws glitter at them. She&nbsp;
explains to him that the song they're listening&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:06.880
to is the one she wants to be played during her&nbsp;
wedding, which she'll have when she finally finds&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:06.880 --> 00:10:12.240
her prince. Brent isn't her prince, however, so&nbsp;
she asks her dad to dance with her instead. Lola&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:12.240 --> 00:10:16.480
tells Eric he is her prince, always has been, and&nbsp;
there will be nobody good enough to ever replace&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:16.480 --> 00:10:22.000
him. She closes her eyes and leans in for a kiss&nbsp;
- Eric hesitates at first, but as he gives up and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:26.480
leans in to kiss Lola, they're cut off by Brent&nbsp;
making noise - he's noticed his razor blade on the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:31.040
chair and he's sat on it on purpose to hide it.
