00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:35.680
Mr Valentine - the cop promises he's sent out an&nbsp;
investigation team and will contact her if he has&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:35.680 --> 00:10:40.560
any news. Holly returns to Brent's room and, after&nbsp;
failing to contact her mother on the phone because&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:40.560 --> 00:10:45.280
of the late hours, she cries her heart off.
At Lola's, we see Eric chopping the head off the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:45.280 --> 00:10:49.280
roadkill they picked up later and passing the body&nbsp;
to his daughter before grabbing a bucket of water.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:53.600
Under Brent's watching eyes and while he tries&nbsp;
once again to cut the rope with his blade,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:53.600 --> 00:10:57.120
they go into the living room and move the&nbsp;
carpet to reveal a secret door on the floor.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:10:57.840 --> 00:11:01.040
Screeching from various creatures can be&nbsp;
heard when they open it to feed them with&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:01.040 --> 00:11:05.040
the animal and throw the water at them.
A little image parallelism occurs then:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:05.040 --> 00:11:08.640
Eric leaves the house to grab his tools at&nbsp;
the same time a professor leaves the school&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:08.640 --> 00:11:13.360
to find Jaime and Mia making love inside the car.&nbsp;
After the couple is kicked out by their teacher,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:18.240
we go back to Eric, who hands his electric drill&nbsp;
to Lola so she can drill a hole on Brent's head.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:22.720
After doing so twice, they start pouring hot&nbsp;
water into it, revealing the procedure behind what&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:22.720 --> 00:11:27.520
happened to Bright Eyes: lobotomization. Luckily&nbsp;
Brent manages to finish cutting the rope tying&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:31.520
his hand before they're done, and he pushes them&nbsp;
away from him before grabbing the falling drill to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:31.520 --> 00:11:35.680
cut the rope on his ankles, then proceeds to use&nbsp;
to knife he takes off his feet to use it on Eric&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:35.680 --> 00:11:41.680
repeatedly. Furious, Carla jumps on him, but he&nbsp;
manages to shake her off before going after Eric.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:41.680 --> 00:11:45.280
He pushes him inside the pit and watches how&nbsp;
the creatures -who turn out to be the previous&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:45.280 --> 00:11:49.520
lobotomized victims- feed on him. As Brent&nbsp;
stares at the horrifying scene in front of&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:49.520 --> 00:11:54.320
him with disgust, Lola approaches him from behind&nbsp;
and pushes him into the pit as well. Getting even&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:58.720
angrier when she realizes she can't save her dad,&nbsp;
she starts throwing things into the pit before&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:11:58.720 --> 00:12:03.120
closing it. Some of those things turn out to be&nbsp;
the flashlight and the hammer, which Brent uses&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:03.120 --> 00:12:07.040
to defend himself from the other victims, leaving&nbsp;
him as the only living being left in there.&nbsp;

00:12:07.760 --> 00:12:11.040
Back in town, Jaime takes an&nbsp;
exhausted Mia back to her house,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:11.040 --> 00:12:16.000
trying not to look suspicious or awkward in front&nbsp;
of her father. Another parallelism occurs here:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:20.320
as Lola checks on Bright Eyes, Mr Valentine&nbsp;
goes inside the house to check on Mia,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:20.320 --> 00:12:25.520
who is crying in her bedroom, wondering why "he"&nbsp;
isn't found. He goes back to his own bedroom then,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:25.520 --> 00:12:29.360
and he tells his wife Mia is fine while looking&nbsp;
at a picture on his night table: it's Timmy&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:29.360 --> 00:12:34.160
Valentine, the victim that escaped - his son and&nbsp;
Mia's brother, the boy she's asking to be found.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:34.800 --> 00:12:38.880
Another revelation happens while Lola puts a&nbsp;
pillow on Bright Eye's face to get rid of her:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:38.880 --> 00:12:43.600
the woman had been Lola's mother. Speaking of&nbsp;
revelations, Holly has one while sleeping on&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:43.600 --> 00:12:48.320
Brent's bed: he remembers him mentioning Lola's&nbsp;
failed invitation to prom, so she decides to call&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:48.320 --> 00:12:53.440
Mr Valentine and inform him of this. Mr Valentine&nbsp;
quickly gets in his car and drives to Lola's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:57.840
house, where he breaks in after seeing the blood&nbsp;
on the floor through the window. He manages to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:57.840 --> 00:13:02.240
find the pit thanks to the noises Brent is making&nbsp;
by throwing bones at the doors, but right after he&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:06.800
opens it, Lola appears behind him and pushes&nbsp;
him in as he did with Brent. She walks back&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:06.800 --> 00:13:10.400
when he tries to shoot her with the officer's&nbsp;
gun then grabs the knife and Brent's necklace,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:10.400 --> 00:13:14.880
which she puts around her own neck. Before leaving&nbsp;
the house, she tells Brent that she'll go after&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:14.880 --> 00:13:20.160
Carla and Holly to hurt them like Brent hurt her&nbsp;
and her dad. The doors of the pit are left open.&nbsp;

00:13:20.160 --> 00:13:24.720
Morning comes. Brent is still in the pit, and&nbsp;
after watching the piles of bones for a while,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:30.560
he gets an idea. As this happens, Lola is walking&nbsp;
along the road, barefoot, shoes and scrapbook one&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:35.440
hand, knife on the other. When she sees a car in&nbsp;
the distance she quickly realizes that's Holly,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:39.760
who never heard back from Mr Valentine. She&nbsp;
throws the scrapbook at her car to make her&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:39.760 --> 00:13:43.040
stop then jumps in to attack Holly.
While the girls struggle in a fight,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:43.040 --> 00:13:47.680
Brent is creating a pile of bones and bones that&nbsp;
help him climb out of the pit. He wastes no time&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:47.680 --> 00:13:53.200
in escaping by using the police car Mr Valentine&nbsp;
had arrived with, driving at an insane speed. In a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:53.200 --> 00:13:57.760
matter of seconds, he makes it to the spot on the&nbsp;
road where Lola is chasing Holly - Brent quickly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:13:57.760 --> 00:14:02.960
recognizes his girlfriend and drives around her,&nbsp;
hitting Lola instead. As soon as he stops the car,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:02.960 --> 00:14:07.680
Holly gets inside and cries when she realizes&nbsp;
who is driving. They take a moment to reunite&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:11.760
and bask in each other's presence, but they're&nbsp;
interrupted by the painful groans of Lola, who&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:11.760 --> 00:14:16.240
is dragging herself on the road behind them, knife&nbsp;
still in hand because she still wants her revenge.&nbsp;

00:14:16.240 --> 00:14:20.400
Brent sees her and after sharing a look with&nbsp;
Holly, he doesn't hesitate: he starts the car&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:20.400 --> 00:14:25.440
to run over her. Lola watches her end come to&nbsp;
her in slow motion. With the danger and horrors&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:14:25.440 --> 00:14:30.080
finally over, Brent drives back to his home, where&nbsp;
he and Holly reunite with Carla in a tight hug.

